substep.action:
Compose a markdown block matching the research-finding shape. Format:
```md ### Prototype: {{session.prototype_name}} ({{ISO 8601 datetime}})
**Question answered**: {{session.caller_question}}
**Branch**: {{session.branch}}
**What was built**: {{one-sentence description of the prototype}}
**How it ran**: `{{session.run_command}}` (LOGIC) | "viewed in browser" (UI)
**Findings**: {{numbered factual list of what was observed. Each finding is one or two sentences with no opinions or recommendations. Examples:
1. SQLAlchemy SAVEPOINT-based nested transactions DO work on Postgres; both outer and inner tx report in_transaction()=True. 2. Rolling back the inner transaction (savepoint) does NOT roll back the outer; the outer commits successfully. 3. Sequelize-style nested-tx semantics are achievable; no fragile workarounds needed.}}
**Preserved at**: `{{session.prototype_path}}` (refer to this path if the prototype needs to be re-run or inspected in the future)
**Iterations**: {{session.iteration_count + 1}} ```
Store as {{session.findings_block}}.
Findings discipline: - FACTUAL — what was observed, not what should be done - SPECIFIC — cite the run output, the visible state, the user's UI report - SHORT — 3-7 findings max; if more, the question was too broad - NO RECOMMENDATIONS — those belong to ticket-design, not here

substep.template-output:
Prototype session complete.

- Name: {{session.prototype_name}}
- Branch: {{session.branch}}
- Status: {{status}}
- Iterations: {{iteration_count}}
- Preserved at: {{session.prototype_path}}

**Findings block** (returned to caller for inclusion in research file):

{{session.findings_block}}

Caller (ticket-grill) will append this to the bundle's research
file in its own step-05.
